  <p i18n:translate="license.pdtools.zero">Use this universal tool if
    you are a holder of copyright or database rights, and you wish to
    waive all your interests in your work.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a i18n:translate="util.learn_more"
	 href="/about/cc0">Learn more</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a i18n:translate="util.use_this_tool"
	 href="/license/zero/">Use this tool</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 i18n:translate="util.public_domain_certification">Public Domain Certification</h2>

  <p i18n:translate="license.pdtools.pdc">Use this tool if you have
    identified and want to certify other works that are already in the
    public domain.  You will also be relinquishing any rights in the
    work you may have under copyright.  Creative Commons does not
    recommend this tool for use with works under copyright - consider
    using CC0 instead.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <a i18n:translate="util.use_this_tool"
	 href="/license/publicdomain-2">Use this tool</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

